The evidence with the title 'Are increased PERS costs responsible for a $500 per student ... ' says Jan 22, 2013  ... John Kitzhaber says " in this next biennium, the cost of primary and secondary education is going to increase by more that $ 1000 per student. Half of that $1000 – $ 500 per student – is accounted for by the increased cost of PERS alone." 
